cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance analysis of clustered multi-hop relaying wireless networks, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper derives closed-form expressions for the probability distribution of the end-to-end SNR and the system ergodic capacity, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is another likely category as the paper analyzes the performance of wireless networks and derives the system symbol error rate (SER) performance for a wide class of modulation schemes. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper combines ad-hoc routing and cooperative diversity in CDFMR systems, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is the least likely category as there is no mention of multimedia in the paper.
